eq_notes: EEG system returned with quite a bit of crud on it.  Need to emphasize the cleaning procedure better.

rlog_comments: Helped with installing an updated version of the teleBCI guide.    Still lots of problems with the Notepad speller.    Never accepts the first letter.     Sometimes when you clear a word, it appears with the first letter in the next run.    Cuts out mid word!!

The notepad speller went haywire.  It shut down adobe connect and basically locked the computer.  User had to use task manager to turn it off.  Also used task manager to stop the guide, which is why there is no log data.

assess_comments: This technology shows lots of potential for being useful for ALS patients.
nassess_comments: this is more effective than trying to communicate with a patient who has limited movement using an eye gaze or card system

mob_n1_sp_reas_end: No longer walking because of fall.

rlog_comments: Many things wrong with the recording.  Had the amplifier just cut out a few times in different runs.  Made sure that the ground and reference were well connected and gelled.  There was also a low frequency wave which I thought must be a respiratory signal or something else.   Worst in run 6 probably.     Also, was counting to about 2.  increased the on and off time over the course of the session and ended up on 400ms on, 200ms off.  Need to change param files for future sessions.

First full session using 400ms on time and 200ms off time.  Reported counting ~5 flashes.  No noticeable VEP.  Might be a good candidate for audio spelling even though they are able to very coarsely use the eye tracker.

Sometime between sessions, the cable to PO8 severed.  No data in this electrode moving forward.     There was huge oscillation at the beginning, set the filter to 2-60Hz for first run.  Forgot to keep doing this and it reverted to 0.5-60 hz for following runs, but the low freq noise was not apparent.    Also permanently changed the application window size to be 50% larger.      Spelled 3 letters correct in this session, best yet.
Run 5 - Did you grow up in Illinois (YES)?  Beep selected  Run 7 - Did you work for Microsoft (NO)? Selected No Twice!  Run 8 - Were you born in April (YES)?  Selected Yes and a Beep

extension_comments: Although audio system wasn't working more than 50%, the participant team was very interested in continuing their use of the system.

screen_notes: missing download and upload speed, but they have comcast.

log_comments: The patient says it was fun.  The caregiver remarks that Andrew is extremely patient and a great help with my gaining confidence in the various procedures.
rlog_comments: Very frustrating not being able to help with a problem by controlling the computer.  For some reason, when they were sharing their screen -- the computer froze up.  I was not able to take control or even maximize the adobe connect interface
Did excellent work with notepad speller.  Used 8 flashes nearly flawlessly.  Can use 6 flashes next session.

log_comments: A bigger screen for Patty would be nice, but that is in no way connected to the performance of the program - just a personal preference of the operator on this end.
rlog_comments: Helped with charging.    The cap turned off abruptly today.    Not uploading data yet because log file not yet available.

log_helptype_other: Paused session, removed cap and charged Nautilus headset for 30 minutes before resuming session.

log_comments: The last notepad speller run was compromised by Bernie's chin hairs.  The neck brace and chin strap were rubbing against them and became VERY irritating on the last run. I didn't have time to shave him before we started the session.  Will make sure he's clean-shaven for next week.
rlog_comments: DId very well in free spelling up until the last run, which was only 4 flashes per selection.

log_comments: Subject counted all flashes until the last Notepad run.  Overall, we felt pretty good about his performance.

assess_notes_cap: Because my brother's hair is thick and slightly longer than normal and because he has a smaller head, it was sometimes difficult to fit the cap snugly.  In addition, the neck collar he wears to elevate his chin sometimes made it more difficult to attach the Nautilus.
assess_comments: My brother and I thank you for the opportunity to participate in this study.  It helped to put a positive spin on our devastating situation.
